Property, plant, and equipment is stated at original cost or fair value at acquisition, as appropriate, less any regulatory disallowances
and impairments. Original cost may include: materials; labor; minor items of property; appropriate administrative and general
costs; payroll-related costs such as taxes, pensions, and other benefits; and the interest capitalized and/or cost of equity funds used
during construction.
